article.headline: North Texas 69, SE Missouri State 62
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Quincy Williams and Leonard Hopkins scored 14 points apiece for North Texas, which beat Southeast Missouri State 69-62 on Wednesday night. Hopkins was only 2-of-6 from the field but hit 10 of 12 free throws. Michael Jones grabbed nine rebounds and Williams had eight for the Mean Green (6-3), which had a 46-36 rebounding advantage. Dainmon Gonner and Terrick Willoughby each scored 17 points for the Indians (3-6). Reggie Golson grabbed 12 rebounds, and Gonner had 11. Both teams were plagued by poor shooting. Southeast Missouri was 8-of-31 from the field during the first half but trailed by only three at halftime.
